# Commit And Push Runtime Work

When the user asks for runtime/tool changes that must be visible after reinstall or deployment, do not stop at local edits.

- Run focused validation and any required artifact build/update steps.
- Commit the completed changes with a clear message.
- Push the commit to the requested branch/remote when the user explicitly asks for push or says the work is not complete unless pushed.
- If a pushed install/test artifact is needed for reinstall visibility, rebuild/update it before committing.
- Never claim reinstall visibility until the artifact/manifest or deployment path has been updated.
